  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The solar_kpi_monthly view (source: solar_installations) has dimensions: record_date, site_type, region, inverter_status. Measures: total_solar_generation_kwh, avg_panel_efficiency, avg_irradiance, online_site_count, total_site_count. The battery_kpi_monthly view (source: battery_snapshots) has dimensions: snapshot_date, site_type, battery_status. Measures: avg_state_of_charge, avg_battery_health, total_discharge_kwh, total_charge_kwh, fault_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. site_id, site_name).",
